{title: Danville Girl}
{artist: The Greenbriar Boys}
{composer: Written by Vince Martin}

To [D7]carry an empty [G]car
Oh I got off at Danville
Got [C]stuck on a [D7]Danville [G]girl
You can bet your life she's [Em]out of sight
She [A7]wore those Danville [D7]curls
She [G]took me to her parlor
She [C]treated me [D7]nice and [G]kind
She got me in the notion
Of [D7]bumming all the [G]time
She wore her hair on the back of her head
Like [C]high-tone [D7]people [G]do
And the very next train come [Em]down the line
I [A7]bid my girl a[D7]dieu
I [G]pulled my cap down over my eyes
And [C]walked the [D7]railroad [G]track
And [C]there I [G]caught the next freight train
[D7]Never to come [G]back